Here's an example where you parse invalid UTF-8 gracefully:

```rust
let byte_data = vec![240, 159, 146, 170];
match String::from_utf8(byte_data) {
    Ok(s) => println!("UTF-8 string: {}", s),
    Err(e) => match e.utf8_error() {
        std::str::Utf8Error { .. } => {
            println!("Invalid UTF-8 data, cannot convert to string.");
        }
    },
}
```

